   <TEXT>
   <S PAR='1' RSNT='1' SNO='1'>In the fall of man: The divine economy: God promised Adam that Christ would come as the seed of woman to destroy the serpent Satan Gen 3:14-15.</S>
   <S PAR='2' RSNT='1' SNO='2'>God promised to let man have life signifying God's eternal life and provided man with covering typifying God's coming redemption in Christ Gen 3:20-21.</S>
   <S PAR='3' RSNT='1' SNO='3'>The issue of the satanic chaos Gen 3:22-24: The fallen man was driven out from the garden of Eden.</S>
   <S PAR='4' RSNT='1' SNO='4'>The entrance to the tree of life was closed to the fallen man.</S>
   <S PAR='5' RSNT='1' SNO='5'>In the further steps and consummation of man's fall: The divine economy: Abel accepted God's promise in offering the firstlings of his flock typifying Christ to receive God's respect Gen 4:4.</S>
   <S PAR='6' RSNT='1' SNO='6'>Enosh, the fragile man, called on the name of Jehovah for His rich supply Gen 4:26.</S>
   <S PAR='7' RSNT='1' SNO='7'>Enoch walked with God and was taken away by God Gen 5:21-24.</S>
   <S PAR='8' RSNT='1' SNO='8'>Noah walked with God and prepared the ark typifying Christ for the carrying out of the divine economy Gen 6:8-22.</S>
   <S PAR='9' RSNT='1' SNO='9'>Noah built an altar and offered burnt offerings typifying Christ to God to please Him so that the earth could be kept in its systems Gen 8:20-22.</S>
   <S PAR='10' RSNT='1' SNO='10'>The satanic chaos: Cain rejected God's promise and killed his brother Abel, bringing in God's judgment and curse Gen 4:3-16.</S>
   <S PAR='11' RSNT='1' SNO='11'>Man became flesh and man's sin became great, so man was judged by God with the flood Gen 6:3, 5-7, 13; 7:10-11, 17-23a.</S>
   <S PAR='12' RSNT='1' SNO='12'>Man rebelled against God, exalted himself, and worshipped the idols at Babel in union with Satan to frustrate the divine economy Gen 11:1-9.</S>
   </TEXT>
